Real animals were not present in Red and Blue. They're only mentioned in the 1996 pokedex book which may have outdated info.

We know thanks to the late Takeshi Shudo, who wrote the original anime, that they never existed in the Pokémon universe which means they must have been discarded pretty early on. The best evidence comes from Shudo mention that it was decided that Pokémon would mirror real animals in terms of human-pokemon relationships. Thanks to interviews from the late 90s and early 00s we know Satoshi Tajiri was closely involved with the development of the anime.

Pokémon at it's core is about an idealized childhood of a man who spent it exploring nature, capturing, taking care and studying animals. If real animals existed that would only take away from that which according to his biography was the main feeling he wanted to convey with Pokémon.
